rom a moral and an international legal perspective. She discusses moral and international legal limits to state use of lethal force and argues that the moral principles and the international legal regulations allow for the practice only in very specific, very rare, and rather hypothetical cases. The analysis is based on a thorough discussion of the human right to life, the laws and ethics of war, and the relevant moral and legal arguments. This makes it of particular interest to philosophers and legal theorists interested in terrorism, counter-terrorism, human rights, and the legitimacy of defensive state measures.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aTargeted killing. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxLaw and legislation. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxMoral and ethical aspects. 4aConstitutional State. 4aGezielte Tötung. 4aHuman Rights. 4aMenschenrechte. 4aRechtsstaat. 4aTerrorism. 4aTerrorismus. 4aTerrorismusbekämpfung. 70(DE-601)1046371880(DE-588)4068999-2aAusland2gnd 70(DE-601)1054751650(DE-588)4160781-8aHumanitäres Völkerrecht2gnd 70(DE-601)1060885560(DE-588)4074725-6aMenschenrecht2gnd 70(DE-601)1061398860(DE-588)4060336-2aTötung2gnd 70(DE-601)1061432040(DE-588)4059536-5aTerrorist2gnd 70(DE-601)1063359870(DE-588)4015602-3aEthik2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHI